1
00:00:00,599 --> 00:00:02,865
This room is called the baptism room

2
00:00:02,890 --> 00:00:05,000
Or the baptismal font

3
00:00:05,025 --> 00:00:07,318
Shaped like this, in the form of a cup

4
00:00:07,343 --> 00:00:14,166
Here the ceremony is held for a child’s first entry into the church

5
00:00:14,427 --> 00:00:19,843
This is where the baptism ritual takes place, where children are baptized

6
00:00:19,868 --> 00:00:25,260
In this font or this water-filled place

7
00:00:25,285 --> 00:00:29,089
So that the child receives this sacrament and enters Christianity

8
00:00:29,114 --> 00:00:30,677
In this room

9
00:00:30,702 --> 00:00:34,479
In the opposite room

10
00:00:34,504 --> 00:00:38,932
The priest is prepared there

11
00:00:38,957 --> 00:00:41,354
The priest enters from these rooms

12
00:00:41,693 --> 00:00:46,745
The priest’s vestments were kept in these rooms

13
00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:48,776
For celebrating the Mass

14
00:00:48,801 --> 00:00:52,917
Along with the deacons who served the church

15
00:00:52,942 --> 00:00:56,745
They had their own special attire, which they wore here

16
00:00:57,110 --> 00:01:00,261
This, as is clear, is the altar

17
00:01:00,286 --> 00:01:01,719
Destroyed

18
00:01:01,744 --> 00:01:06,875
These arches were arranged in this way

19
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,365
They were destroyed and overturned like this

20
00:01:10,390 --> 00:01:13,334
They were on this façade, this image

21
00:01:13,464 --> 00:01:17,370
And as we see, there are Armenian inscriptions

22
00:01:17,553 --> 00:01:20,756
It is a verse taken from the Holy Gospel

23
00:01:20,781 --> 00:01:23,490
On the main arch

24
00:01:23,515 --> 00:01:26,547
There were chandeliers here

25
00:01:26,808 --> 00:01:33,083
And also the distinctive Armenian crosses were destroyed

26
00:01:33,108 --> 00:01:36,964
In this form, as is clear

27
00:01:36,989 --> 00:01:44,359
There were many icons, private images painted by Armenian artists

28
00:01:44,384 --> 00:01:48,552
In these empty spaces of the church

29
00:01:49,490 --> 00:01:52,745
Interviewer: Can we talk about the destruction

30
00:01:52,770 --> 00:01:55,896
That ISIS inflicted on this hall in general?

31
00:01:55,921 --> 00:02:01,183
As for the destruction, first this altar that was so tall

32
00:02:01,365 --> 00:02:05,609
And this arch was attached to it

33
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:11,521
It was covered with cloths used in the Mass

34
00:02:11,808 --> 00:02:17,094
And here there was a curtain, which is not here now

35
00:02:17,224 --> 00:02:21,938
And as we see, all the crosses were tampered with and destroyed

36
00:02:21,963 --> 00:02:23,474
As is clear

37
00:02:23,499 --> 00:02:27,381
So they could erase these symbols

38
00:02:27,406 --> 00:02:31,391
There was this space

39
00:02:32,771 --> 00:02:38,422
Where a select group of the church’s daughters were seated

40
00:02:38,657 --> 00:02:43,188
The church’s daughters who sang hymns and chanted

41
00:02:43,213 --> 00:02:44,855
What is called the choir

42
00:02:44,959 --> 00:02:46,808
That presented the hymns

43
00:02:46,859 --> 00:02:50,635
Alongside the rituals held in the church
